{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "• The machine bias hypothesis implies both an absence of systematic bias towards a certain population and a low adaptability.",
    "To test the ability of LLMs to simulate human beings, we use the \"silicon sampling\" task implemented by several researchers (Argyle et al., 2023; Santurkar et al., 2023).",
    "The task uses socio-demographic information to condition a large language model to \"think\" as a person with a given profile, then asks the model a survey question.",
    "Insofar as LLMs are tools aimed to predict the next word of a text, the task takes the model's prediction to be the answer of the given social profile to the survey question.",
    "We then compare this silicon answer to a ground truth-the answers given to the same question by human survey respondents."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To test the ability of LLMs to simulate human beings, we use the \"silicon sampling\" task implemented by several researchers (Argyle et al., 2023; Santurkar et al., 2023)."
  ]
}